u03b1 \u03b5k,\u03b1eikx\n\n(50.16)\n\nwhere \u03b5k,\u03b1 for a given k is a set of two orthogonal unit vectors. If A were a general vector field rather than a transverse\n\nfield, then we would have to include a third unit vector.", "embedding": [-0.0009286068, 0.01454935, 0.015961953, -0.0052601015, -0.0040910114, 0.009569543, -0.010279819, -0.01841324, -0.03937092, 0.05108445, 0.025067419, 0.038529795, 0.0051754904, -0.048835702, -0.04926614, 0.022351222, -0.016478755, -0.027351225, -0.091103286, 0.03714952, 0.022663495, 0.01029808, -0.06344399, -0.021049632, -0.0119944615, -0.0032876977, 0.012568902, -0.019442035, 0.03330189, 0.04629694, 0.0324886, 0.0074360874, 0.0026365302, -0.025962826, -0.009125519, 0.021976411, 0.011811734, -0.084743105, 0.022790696, -0.037353184, 0.04938253, -0.01070262, -9.739177e-05, -0.023262588, -0.008375455, -0.00035066466, 0.0073127993, 0.0042024204, -0.024424171, -0.055358082, 0.02764867, 0.015625274, 0.014133013, -0.013277341, -0.00060390285, -0.025452226, -0.008721534, 0.012973557, -0.003285563, 0.012941857, 0.014851437, 0.007686952, 0.01881074, -0.015558834, -0.0036539668, 0.0443692, -0.014048789, 0.07752643, 0.021525832, 0.004338136, 0.0063738204, -0.021348797, 0.0024299424, 0.024136188, -0.038758643, 0.050578725, 0.011165291, -0.06818444, -0.050228287, -0.0069942027, -0.03166125, -0.018828033, -0.01061922, 0.027862523, -0.011215749, -0.017531998, 0.0068120435, -0.0026908587, 0.03933843, 0.014311478, 0.034676563, 0.04798086, -0.021357408, -0.018811103, 0.053578135, 0.020018743, 0.0010135805, 0.030399531, 0.051700473, 0.023070754, 0.005914624, 0.04797011, -0.019178547, 0.046554208, -0.020285895, 0.06668202, -0.015260566, 0.01855554, 0.02339967, -0.057879362, 0.02954878, -0.01925643, -0.005690406, 0.022984311, -0.0017609058, 0.054503236, 0.030073136, 0.0069506913, -0.043146823, -0.013441104, 0.026643459, -0.01491423, 0.02042947, 0.003144819, -0.015884658, 0.008154594, 0.0054180725, 0.00497764, -0.044591248, 0.014961757, 0.020895